HEADWORD: Hydro-aëroplane
<hw>Hy"dro-a"⟦eum⟧r*o*plane`</hw>. <fld>(A⟦eum⟧ronautics)</fld> <def>An
a⟦eum⟧roplane with a boatlike or other understructure that enables it to
travel on, or to rise from the surface of, a body of water by its own
motive power; -- now usually referred to as a
<altname>seaplane</altname>.</def> <mark>[obsolescent]</mark> ⟦br⟧
